cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about semantic segmentation using convolutional networks and bounding box annotations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for semantic segmentation, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of large datasets, which could suggest cs.MM (Multimedia) as a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method, which could suggest cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category.
